[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Summary
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Northumberland County Council covers a large area, including many isolated communities (both in urban and rural areas), hence it is replying to this Inquiry as it is very relevant
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]NCC identifies demand for transport to isolated communities by evaluating demand for services that already exist  
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The extent to which the needs of different groups of passengers can be taken into account is constrained by available budget
[normal]d)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The challenges a
[normal]ssociated with providing better public transport to isolated communities are varied, but the only way they can be overcome is through more, and more consistent, long-term revenue funding 
[normal]e)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Community Transport has a valuable role in meeting the public transp
[normal]ort needs of isolated communities but has constraints. It can be improved by better funding
[normal]f)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The extent to which isolated communities should be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive services should be determined by communities themselves 
[normal]g)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The main challenge to the public transport needs of isolated communities is the need for long-term, consistent revenue funding.
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Northumberland is a large County, comprising both r
[normal]ural and urban communities.  
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is home to 312,000 people and covers 5013 sq km, of which 96.7% is classified as rural.   49% of the population live in rural areas
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]There are important contrasts between the three administrative areas of the County as per t
[normal]he following table
